<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832431>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Phylogenetic hypothesis of Tetralycosa Roewer, 1960 based on 31 morphological and one ecological characters. A. Basal branches including outgroups. B. Terminal salt lake clade (L = 71, Ci = 61, Ri = 80). Bremer support values> 1 are indicated by numbers in squares below the respective node." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3832431/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832435>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Tetralycosa oraria (L. Koch, 1876), ♂ (WAM 71/360) and female (WAM 71/361). A–B. Male carapace, lateral and frontal view. C–D. Left male pedipalp, ventral and retrolateral view. E. Left male pedipalp, palea section of bulbus, ventral view. F–G. Female epigyne, dorsal and ventral view. Scale bar: A = 4.42 mm; B = 1.88 mm; C–D = 1.28 mm; E = 0.56 mm; F–G = 0.89 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3832435/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832455>
    dc:description "Fig. 15. Tetralycosa alteripa (McKay, 1976), ♂ (WAM T47354) and ♀, paratype (WAM T47356). A. Male carapace, lateral view. B–C. Left male pedipalp, ventral and retrolateral view. D. Left male pedipalp, palea section of bulbus, ventral view. E–F. Female epigyne, ventral and dorsal view. Scale bar: A = 8.83 mm; B–C = 2.56 mm; D = 1.47 mm; E–F = 1.91 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3832455/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

